        "comment": {
            "name": "comment",
            "type": "com.atlassian.jira.issue.fields.CommentSystemField",
            "value": [
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/49496",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=matthew",
                        "name": "matthew",
                        "displayName": "Matthew Weier O'Phinney",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "By marking the element as optional (i.e., not required), you're telling the validation chain that if no value is provided, then it validates -- in other words, it does not need to run any additional validators. Mark the element as required if you have validators that must be run.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=matthew",
                        "name": "matthew",
                        "displayName": "Matthew Weier O'Phinney",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2012-01-13T14:44:18.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2012-01-13T14:44:18.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/49497",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=tomykaira",
                        "name": "tomykaira",
                        "displayName": "Hiroshi TOMITA",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "If an element is marked as required, it should not be empty.\r\nIn my case, sometimes empty value is accepted, and in other cases not.\r\n\r\nI found a workaround (following), but this is ugly, and difference between \"required\" and \"notAllowEmpty\" is ambiguous.\r\n\r\n    $elm->setAllowEmpty(false)\r\n        ->setAutoInsertNotEmptyValidator(false)\r\n\r\nCould be good solution?",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=tomykaira",
                        "name": "tomykaira",
                        "displayName": "Hiroshi TOMITA",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2012-01-13T14:53:38.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2012-01-13T14:53:38.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/49498",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=matthew",
                        "name": "matthew",
                        "displayName": "Matthew Weier O'Phinney",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Your use case is exactly why we have those settings.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=matthew",
                        "name": "matthew",
                        "displayName": "Matthew Weier O'Phinney",
                        "active": true
                    },
